      <!-- COPD-specific clinical pearls -->
      <section id="clinical-pearls" style="margin-bottom:2.25rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; margin-bottom:0.85rem; padding-bottom:0.4rem; border-bottom:2px solid #e2e8f0;">
          COPD-Specific Clinical Pearls for Concept Map Construction
        </h2>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.6rem;">
          {[
            { colour: '#fef2f2', border: '#fecaca', dot: '⚠️', label: 'Oxygen target 88–92%, not 94–98%', detail: 'Patients with chronic hypercapnia and elevated bicarbonate (as seen in Mr. Holloway: HCO₃ 30) may depend on hypoxic drive. Excessive oxygen can suppress ventilatory drive, worsen hypercapnia, and precipitate respiratory failure. Always document the target SpO₂ range in your concept map outcomes.' },
            { colour: '#fefce8', border: '#fde68a', dot: '💊', label: 'Inhaler non-adherence is a modifiable precipitant', detail: 'COPD exacerbations frequently result from maintenance inhaler non-adherence. Identifying this during Phase 1 (Deficient Knowledge cluster) allows the student nurse to address both the immediate crisis and its root cause — a powerful example of holistic, preventive nursing practice.' },
            { colour: '#f0fdf4', border: '#bbf7d0', dot: '🫁', label: 'Pursed-lip breathing is an independent, evidence-based intervention', detail: 'PLB prolongs exhalation, creates auto-PEEP, reduces air-trapping, and has been shown to improve SpO₂ and reduce dyspnoea in COPD. It is within the independent nursing scope of practice — no order required — making it a high-value concept map intervention.' },
            { colour: '#eff6ff', border: '#bfdbfe', dot: '🔗', label: 'Dx 2 directly worsens Dx 1 — bidirectional arrows matter', detail: 'Retained secretions worsen ventilation-perfusion mismatch (Dx 2 → worsens → Dx 1). Treating airway clearance is therefore not just about comfort: it is a direct intervention on gas exchange. The concept map makes this clinical logic visible.' },
            { colour: '#fff7ed', border: '#fed7aa', dot: '😰', label: 'Anxiety in dyspnoea: non-pharmacological first', detail: 'Benzodiazepines carry respiratory depression risk in COPD. Evidence-based non-pharmacological interventions — cool fan to the face, pursed-lip breathing, upright positioning, calm presence — should be trialled first and documented in the concept map before pharmacological anxiolysis is considered.' },
            { colour: '#faf5ff', border: '#e9d5ff', dot: '🧪', label: 'Penicillin allergy constrains antibiotic selection', detail: 'Many macrolide or fluoroquinolone antibiotics are used for COPD exacerbation with concurrent pneumonia. Document the allergy prominently on the concept map — it affects dependent interventions and requires collaborative communication with the pharmacist and physician.' },
          ].map(({ colour, border, dot, label, detail }) => (
            <div style={`background:${colour}; border:1px solid ${border}; border-radius:0.5rem; padding:0.85rem 1rem;`}>
              <p style="font-weight:700; color:#1e293b; font-size:0.9rem; margin-bottom:0.3rem;">{dot} {label}</p>
              <p style="color:#475569; font-size:0.875rem; margin:0; line-height:1.65;">{detail}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

